        "content": "*“ReFi is about regenerating the social fabric while creating coordinated environmental frameworks and grassroots economics. It’s weaving passion into systems for real-world impact.”* \n\n### **Founding Story & Key Motivations**\n\nReFi Mexico emerged in March 2023 when Gerardo Alvarez and Oscar joined forces after an IRL MotusDAO event. Inspired by the “regenassance,” they envisioned aligning Bancambio and MotusDAO’s ideas to contribute to the global shift towards regenerative economies. The first steps included applying to Gitcoin’s #GG17 round and hosting IRL gatherings to cultivate the solarpunk movement in Mexico.\n\nTheir aim is to build a robust regenerative framework across Mexico by uniting Web3 technologies with grassroots initiatives.\n\n### **What Makes ReFi Mexico Special**\n\nReFi Mexico bridges grassroots regeneration and innovative digital frameworks. As a “connection hub,” the node builds collaborations between organic farmers, water harvesting systems, and clean energy solutions, intending to integrate these efforts on-chain. Its unique Impact Market Maker project is pioneering secure funding for impact DAOs in Mexico, gaining traction as a replicable model for other nodes globally.\n\n![GFspeoDW4AI1FPn.jpeg](nodes/refi-mexico/images/cover.jpeg)\n\n## 2024 Highlights\n\n### Building the Impact Market Maker\n\n- **What Happened:** Developed the front end for an innovative framework enabling local communities to tokenise their impact. Work on back-end and smart contracts is ongoing.\n- **Why It Matters:** The Impact Market Maker offers a scalable solution for funding grassroots impact DAOs, positioning ReFi Mexico as a leader in regenerative finance tools.\n\n### Hosting IRL Experiments\n\n- **What Happened:** Two live Impact Market experiments tested wallet onboarding and real-world on-chain transactions with local vendors and impact agents.\n- **Why It Matters:** These events proved the feasibility of blockchain tools in fostering collaboration and practical impact, providing insights to refine the Impact Market Maker.\n\n### Mentoring Impact Projects\n\n- **What Happened:** Supported Huautli Libre, Pluviam, and ReFi Phangan with Web3 integration and strategy. ReFi Phangan transitioned its NFT model to “Impact Products,” inspired by ReFi Mexico.\n- **Why It Matters:** These collaborations showcased how Web3 tools can be adapted to diverse sectors, reinforcing ReFi Mexico’s role as a knowledge hub for regenerative innovation.\n\n### Partnerships and Advocacy\n\n- **What Happened:** Forged partnerships with Ethereum Mexico, Near Protocol, and Celo Mexico, while advocating for a Celo Mexican Peso stablecoin to support local regenerative projects.\n- **Why It Matters:** Partnerships expand ReFi Mexico’s reach and credibility while aligning with global blockchain ecosystems to ensure long-term relevance and impact.\n\n## Vision for 2025\n\n### Launching Impact Market Maker\n\n- **What’s Coming:** Finalise back-end development and smart contracts to launch the tool with three pilot communities. Integrate the Celo Mexican Peso stablecoin for seamless transactions.\n- **Why It Matters:**The tool empowers communities to tokenise impact and access funding, establishing a replicable framework for grassroots regeneration.\n\n### Expanding Partnerships and Community Engagement\n\n- **What’s Coming:** Host hackathons, IRL events, and workshops to onboard new stakeholders and scale partnerships with grassroots initiatives.\n- **Why It Matters:** Strengthening community ties ensures sustainability, while new partnerships expand the node’s reach and funding opportunities.\n\n### Mentorship Programs and Workshops\n\n- **What’s Coming:** Offer workshops to businesses and communities on creating Impact DAOs and using blockchain tools for regeneration.\n- **Why It Matters:** These programs empower communities and generate revenue, supporting financial sustainability while building local capacity.\n\n### Becoming a Regional Hub for ReFi\n\n- **What’s Coming:** Establish a hub for regenerative innovation, supporting grassroots funding mechanisms and attracting venture capital to scale impact solutions\n- **Why It Matters:** A regional hub amplifies ReFi Mexico’s influence and shares its tools with the global movement, accelerating the transition to regenerative economies.\n\n![GYB4CuWbIAAq3P9.jpeg](nodes/refi-mexico/images/refi-mexico6.jpeg)\n\n![Gd6kvO6bcAAMmlz.jpeg](nodes/refi-mexico/images/refi-mexico2.jpeg)\n\n![GYBzmgOb0AAG37z.jpeg](nodes/refi-mexico/images/refi-mexico7.jpeg)\n\n![GYB4CuWb0AQtnIK.jpeg](nodes/refi-mexico/images/refi-mexico5.jpeg)\n\n![GJrY6dNaYAA3SNo.jpeg](nodes/refi-mexico/images/refi-mexico4.jpeg)\n\n![GGttCPrWoAALuV8.jpeg](nodes/refi-mexico/images/refi-mexico3.jpeg)\n\n![GCdJeLzbIAARj8i.jpeg](nodes/refi-mexico/images/refi-mexico1.jpeg)"
